{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J4dm2o6yimq7LixbHf6y6z","type":"tool_result","content":"185\tRead more about how Route Handlers [complement your frontend application](/docs/app/guides/backend-for-frontend), or explore the Route Handlers [API Reference](/docs/app/api-reference/file-conventions/route).\n186\t\n187\t### Route Context Helper\n188\t\n189\tIn TypeScript, you can type the `context` parameter for Route Handlers with the globally available [`RouteContext`](/docs/app/api-reference/file-conventions/route#route-context-helper) helper:\n190\t\n191\t```ts filename=\"app/users/[id]/route.ts\" switcher\n192\timport type { NextRequest } from 'next/server'\n193\t\n194\texport async function GET(_req: NextRequest, ctx: RouteContext<'/users/[id]'>) {\n195\t  const { id } = await ctx.params\n196\t  return Response.json({ id })\n197\t}\n198\t```\n199\t\n200\t> **Good to know**\n201\t>\n202\t> - Types are generated during `next dev`, `next build` or `next typegen`.\n203\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecbd025d-b405-4299-ae88-b098a557b73e","uuid":"a6d84abf-b306-4ce6-b2bb-b9309fb76055","timestamp":"2026-04-15T13:59:34.421Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/node_modules/next/dist/docs/01-app/01-getting-started/15-route-handlers.md","content":"Read more about how Route Handlers [complement your frontend application](/docs/app/guides/backend-for-frontend), or explore the Route Handlers [API Reference](/docs/app/api-reference/file-conventions/route).\n\n### Route Context Helper\n\nIn TypeScript, you can type the `context` parameter for Route Handlers with the globally available [`RouteContext`](/docs/app/api-reference/file-conventions/route#route-context-helper) helper:\n\n```ts filename=\"app/users/[id]/route.ts\" switcher\nimport type { NextRequest } from 'next/server'\n\nexport async function GET(_req: NextRequest, ctx: RouteContext<'/users/[id]'>) {\n  const { id } = await ctx.params\n  return Response.json({ id })\n}\n```\n\n> **Good to know**\n>\n> - Types are generated during `next dev`, `next build` or `next typegen`.\n","numLines":19,"startLine":185,"totalLines":203}}}
