{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ErtXVvPr3LXXAt6APT2npY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GiNNEQQF62TABjXukJW5CA","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/ISSUES.md","content":"## F13 – getUserProfile null detection for missing users\n\n`min(DateTime64)` in ClickHouse returns the epoch (`1970-01-01 00:00:00.000`) rather than\n`NULL` when the aggregation runs over an empty result set (non-nullable column type).\nChecking `statsRows[0].first_seen === null` would therefore never return `null` for a\nmissing user. Decision: include `count() AS event_count` in the stats query and check\n`Number(event_count) === 0` to detect the \"no events found\" case. The unit test was\nupdated to reflect this (mock returns `{ event_count: 0, first_seen: epoch, ... }`).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":308,"cache_read_input_tokens":118985,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":308},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecbd025d-b405-4299-ae88-b098a557b73e","uuid":"38672b23-f54c-4763-bcac-237c702a101d"}
