{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kagej5HLq8ejasevq1GJcg","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t## F2 – TCP vs HTTP port mismatch for `./clickhouse client --port`\n2\t\n3\t`CLICKHOUSE_URL` (e.g. `http://localhost:8123`) uses the HTTP port, but `./clickhouse client`\n4\tconnects via the native TCP protocol whose default port is **9000**, not 8123.\n5\t\n6\t`scripts/migrate.ts` passes whatever port appears in `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to `--port`, so a default\n7\t`CLICKHOUSE_URL` of `http://localhost:8123` will tell the client to connect on TCP port 8123, which\n8\twill fail if ClickHouse is listening on the native TCP port 9000.\n9\t\n10\t**Decision**: keep the current behaviour (pass the URL port as-is) so the env var controls the\n11\tport explicitly. Operators running a non-default setup must set `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to the native TCP\n12\tport (e.g. `http://localhost:9000`) when using `pnpm migrate`. The default local setup with the\n13\tbundled binary uses port 9000 for native TCP — adjust `CLICKHOUSE_URL` or set `--port` separately\n14\tif needed. This is an integration concern; unit tests are not affected.\n15\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecbd025d-b405-4299-ae88-b098a557b73e","uuid":"88d435d1-7d7e-4ca0-9564-a3a32614f0bd","timestamp":"2026-04-15T14:09:22.027Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/ISSUES.md","content":"## F2 – TCP vs HTTP port mismatch for `./clickhouse client --port`\n\n`CLICKHOUSE_URL` (e.g. `http://localhost:8123`) uses the HTTP port, but `./clickhouse client`\nconnects via the native TCP protocol whose default port is **9000**, not 8123.\n\n`scripts/migrate.ts` passes whatever port appears in `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to `--port`, so a default\n`CLICKHOUSE_URL` of `http://localhost:8123` will tell the client to connect on TCP port 8123, which\nwill fail if ClickHouse is listening on the native TCP port 9000.\n\n**Decision**: keep the current behaviour (pass the URL port as-is) so the env var controls the\nport explicitly. Operators running a non-default setup must set `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to the native TCP\nport (e.g. `http://localhost:9000`) when using `pnpm migrate`. The default local setup with the\nbundled binary uses port 9000 for native TCP — adjust `CLICKHOUSE_URL` or set `--port` separately\nif needed. This is an integration concern; unit tests are not affected.\n","numLines":15,"startLine":1,"totalLines":15}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Tz1bttrkZYUt3X7NHJSYQM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UxMuHjB9Z51U1VPYHoMGGK","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/ISSUES.md","old_string":"## F2 – TCP vs HTTP port mismatch for `./clickhouse client --port`","new_string":"## F13 – getUserProfile null detection for missing users\n\n`min(DateTime64)` in ClickHouse returns the epoch (`1970-01-01 00:00:00.000`) rather than\n`NULL` when the aggregation runs over an empty result set (non-nullable column type).\nChecking `statsRows[0].first_seen === null` would therefore never detect a missing user.\nDecision: include `count() AS event_count` in the stats query and check\n`Number(event_count) === 0` to detect \"no events found\". The unit test was updated to mock\n`{ event_count: 0, first_seen: epoch, ... }` to match this behaviour.\n\n## F2 – TCP vs HTTP port mismatch for `./clickhouse client --port`"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":728,"cache_read_input_tokens":119873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":728},"output_tokens":59,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecbd025d-b405-4299-ae88-b098a557b73e","uuid":"4db91b8b-c05f-4c65-b7e3-69574dc3c756"}
